      "culturalSignificance": "The Ganges is the most sacred and revered river in Hinduism, central to religious practice and cultural identity for hundreds of millions of people. Cities along the Ganges, especially Varanasi, are major pilgrimage destinations. The Kumbh Mela, held at Ganges confluences, is the largest religious gathering on earth. Ganga water is used in pujas and ceremonies throughout India and the diaspora. The river has inspired countless works of art, literature, and music. Despite modern environmental challenges, the Ganges remains a living goddess and a powerful symbol of Hindu spirituality."
